
					 Ruby-WordNet Installation Instructions
									  $Id: INSTALL,v 1.1 2002/01/05 13:29:40 deveiant Exp $

These instructions are also decidedly Unix-biased. I apologize to those of you
trying to run this on some other platform. Suggestions or patches for
other-platform compatibility are welcome at <ged@FaerieMUD.org>.


Prerequisites
-------------

Versions listed are the ones I've tested with. Earlier versions may work, but
your mileage may vary.

* Ruby (>= 1.6.5)
  Home page: http://www.ruby-lang.org/
  Download: ftp://ftp.ruby-lang.org/pub/ruby/ruby-1.6.5.tar.gz

* WordNet (>= 1.7)
  Home page: http://www.cogsci.princeton.edu/~wn/
  Download: http://www.cogsci.princeton.edu/~wn/obtain/

* Lingua::Wordnet (for now)
  CPAN: http://search.cpan.org/search?dist=Lingua-Wordnet

* bdb (>=0.2.5)
  RAA: http://www.ruby-lang.org/en/raa-list.rhtml?name=bdb
  Download: ftp://moulon.inra.fr/pub/ruby/


Installation
------------

These instructions assume that you've already installed the prerequisite
packages, unpacked the distribution somewhere, and have changed your working
directory to the resultant subdirectory.

To run unit tests (requires RUnit and walkit):

  $ ruby test.rb

To install:

  $ ruby install.rb


Documentation
-------------

If you have Rdoc installed, you can create HTML documentation thusly:

 $ rdoc lib

This will leave HTML documentation in 'doc'.



